items.title: Quincy Jones Essentials
items.description: Quincy Jones (1933 - 2024) was one of modern music's greatest pioneers. He was nominated for 80 Grammys, won 28 and earned a Grammy Legend Award in 1991. Rock with the best of Quincy. (Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Produced By: Quincy Jones
items.description: Quincy Jones (1933-2024) was the definition of a musical genius. Not only has his music stood the test of time, his production work for some of the greatest artists of all times has as well. Make sure you give this playlist multiple listens – you may catch something you missed on the first go-around. (Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Sampling: Quincy Jones
items.description: There's no doubting Quincy Jones' influence on all music. When it comes to hip-hop, Quincy has created numerous memorable moments: From his sampled songs as a performer or a producer, to founding one of hip-hop's most loved mags, Q has done it all. To celebrate his life and legacy, check out Quincy's tracks and the hip-hop songs they shaped. (Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Quincy Jones Live Essentials
items.description: A collection of Quincy Jones' live audio essentials. (Photo: Getty Images)

items.title: Kris Kristofferson Essentials
items.description: Iconic songwriter, country singer and actor Kris Kristofferson (1936 - 2024) was famous for classic songs such as "Me and Bobby McGee", "Sunday Mornin' Comin' Down", "Help Me Make It Through the Night", and numerous others. Kristofferson started out as a songwriter in Nashville in the 1960s, and released is debut solo album in 1970. He joined The Highwaymen together with Willie Nelson, Johnny Cash and Waylon Jennings in 1985. (Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Frankie Beverly & Maze Essentials
items.description: When it comes to smooth R&B grooves, the legendary Frankie Beverly & Maze are amongst the elite. The group started off as Raw Soul before Marvin Gaye recommended a name change. Reminisce on the classics from the legendary band. Rest in peace to Frankie Beverly (1946-2024), who with Maze gave us soul classics like "Joy and Pain" and "Before I Let Go." (Photo: Rovi)

items.title: The Jackson 5 Essentials
items.description: Founded by the Jackson family in Gary, Indiana in 1964. Original members consisted of brothers Jackie, Tito (1953-2024), Jermaine, Marlon and Michael (1958-2009). In the 1970s, the Jackson 5 delivered classics like "ABC," "I'll Be There," and "Never Can Say Goodbye." The group eventually became the Jacksons, and in 1979, Michael broke out in a big way with "Don't Stop 'Til You Get Enough." (Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Beyoncé Essentials
items.description: Since her 2003 debut ‘Dangerously In Love,’ Beyoncé's catalog has been filled with nothing but hits. Get in formation with Queen Bey's highlight reel. (Photo: Columbia)

items.title: Kygo Essentials
items.description: Breaking through in the EDM world in 2014, Kygo has had an astronomical rise to the top of the dance music world. Arguably the king of tropical house, the award winning DJ/producer is one of the world's most in demand artists. Listen to the best songs from the Norwegian artist here, including some star-studded guest performances.

items.title: Kendrick Lamar Essentials
items.description: Kung Fu Kenny has been hitting us with bars since being the rap game's good kid from Compton. Sit down, be humble and listen to Kendrick Lamar's finest. (Photo: pgLang)

items.title: Sérgio Mendes Essencial
items.description: From his debut with the album Dance Moderno in 1961, Sérgio Mendes built a successful career: He helped introduce Bossa Nova to the world with his Brasil '64, released over thirty albums and collaborated with many artists, including Stevie Wonder and the Black Eyed Peas. This playlist features the greatest hits of the artist who traveled the world but never lost the musical flair that's uniquely Brazilian! (Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Rich Homie Quan Essentials
items.description: The late Rich Homie Quan was a beloved artist from Atlanta. He captivated audiences for nearly a decade with his unforgettable music, from chart-topping radio hits to infectious club anthems such as "Type Of Way", "Walk Thru," and "Flex". (Photo: Getty Images)

items.title: New Arrivals
items.description: Dig into fresh new releases with this playlist highlighting the most notable songs in a broad range of genres. (Cover: FKA twigs / Photo: Jordan Hemmingway)

items.title: New Arrivals: Hip-Hop and R&B
items.description: The number one source for the best new Hip-Hop and R&B. (Cover: Sexyy Red & Bruno Mars // Photo: gamma., Press)

items.title: New Arrivals: Pop and R&B
items.description: This playlist highlights the newest and standout Pop and R&B releases of the week. (Cover: Alessia Cara / Jordan Adetunji // Photo: Def Jam, Press / 300 Entertainment, Press)

items.title: New Arrivals: Hip-Hop and Latin
items.description: Hip-hop culture is universal and it's evident in the way we consume music today. With the influx of Latinx stars (Nicky Jam, J Balvin, Bad Bunny) on the charts and collaborating with their fellow mainstream hip-hop MCs (Drake, Cardi B, Meek Mill), it only made sense to combine the worlds. Because at the end of the day, it's all hip-hop, baby. Listen to the best new Hip-Hop & Latin music releases. Playlist previously known as Dímelo Flow. (Cover: Lil Wayne & Tyga // Photo: EMPIRE, Press)

items.title: Guest Verses: Fatman Scoop
items.description: There is no other voice that is distinctive and energetic as Fatman Scoop's. Every artist who wants a bonafide party starter lends their track to Fatman Scoop to add on his ad-libs and chants that pulls all audiences in. Turn up to his guest verses, pop-up appearances, and featured spotlights. (Photo: Getty)

items.title: Linkin Park Essentials
items.description: Formed in 1996, Linkin Park is a rock band hailing from Agoura Hills, California. Known for their genre-bending sound, the band's meteoric rise came in conjunction with the astonishing rise of rap-rock in the early and mid-2000's. Though in league with groups like Korn and Limp Bizkit, Linkin Park's distinct take on rap-rock, one directing heightened attention to the unique dynamic between rapper Mike Shinoda and singer Chester Bennington, has set the band apart from its peers from the release of their 'Hybrid Theory' debut in 2000 onwards. Bennington passed away on July 20, 2017. In 2024, Emily Armstrong of the band Dead Sara was announced as their new singer. (Photo: James Minchin III)

items.title: Maxwell Essentials
items.description: Maxwell's brand of sexy R&B has been love's soundtrack since his highly successful 1996 debut 'Maxwell's Urban Hang Suite.' Dive into these Maxwell necessities. (Photo: BMG, Press)

items.title: Celtic Roots
items.description: The evolving sound of Anglo-Irish roots music, innovators and traditionalists, torchbearers and experimentalists, side by side. (Cover: Anna B. Savage / Photo: Katie Silvester, press)

items.title: Rock Britannia
items.description: A finely tuned selection of the biggest rock acts, as well as some up and coming stars, from the U.K. and Ireland. Loud guitars, catchy choruses and great hooks all over. (Cover: Mogwai / Photo: Steve Gullick)

items.title: Art Rock
items.description: Explore the outer limits of alternative music with this playlist of experimental, noisy avant-rock, post-punk, post-rock, and other exciting, mind-bending sounds of today. (Cover: Mogwai / Photo: Steve Gullick)

items.title: Hot Rocks: Best New Rock
items.description: All the new, hot rock releases you need in your everyday life, from mainstream to alternative, from soft to loud. (Cover: DOROTHY & Slash / Photo: Roc Nation, press)

items.title: Crossroads: Best New Blues
items.description: The best of new blues music, from beloved veterans and exciting newcomers. (Cover: Larkin Poe / Photo: Red Light, press)

items.title: Folk Underground
items.description: New voices, established talent and exciting releases from the fringes of today's folk music and rural improvisation. Far out and deeply rooted, ethereal and mind-bending at the same time. (Cover: Sam Amidon / Photo: Gullick, press)

items.title: Indie Folk & In-Between
items.description: Some of the finest new songs in indie, folk and whatever's in-between. (Cover: The Head and the Heart / Photo: Jasper Graham, press)

items.title: Roots Redux
items.description: Where folk music meets soul and vintage R&B, roots of blues, jazz, gospel and more. (Cover: Sunny War / Photo: Joshua Black Wilkins, New West, press)

items.title: Alt Classics
items.description: All your favourite indie and alt-rock classics in one place. (Cover: James Murphy (LCD Soundsystem) - celebrating 'LCD Soundsystem' @ 20 / Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Indie Britain
items.description: A selection of the exciting sounds of the fresh British/Irish indie scene. Covering everything from punk, rock, indie folk/pop/rock and singer/songwriters from the UK and Ireland. (Cover: Ex-Vöid / Photo: Jody Evans)

items.title: Awesome Americana
items.description: A continuously updated and hand-picked playlist of handcrafted masterpieces from recent years. From mellow singer-songwriters and blue collar rockers to American primitivists and soulful singers, from bearers of proud traditions to the ones paving ways for a new future: This is a slice of Awesome Americana. (Cover :MJ Lenderman // Photo: Josh Kerr, press)

items.title: Classic Rock Classics
items.description: Just what you need when you're looking for all those classic-rock hits and choice deep cuts you grew up with. (Cover: Bob Dylan - celebrating 'Blood On The Tracks' @ 50 / Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Metal Classics
items.description: A rough guide to five decades of hard rock and metal. (Cover: TOOL - celebrating Adam Jones @ 60 / Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Out There: Best New Jazz
items.description: Groundbreaking art is often defined by its inability to be categorized. We highlight sonic shards mined from the vast terrain of new jazz and jazz-adjacent music, from the experimental to the straight-up grooving. (Cover: Hiromi and Sonicwonder / Photo: Mitsuru Nishimura)

items.title: Vocal Jazz
items.description: Enjoy selected highlights of timeless vocal jazz, from legendary crooners to modern-day singers. (Cover: Kandace Springs / Photo: Bob Palmieri)

items.title: Singer-Songwriter Classics
items.description: Tune in, lean back and enjoy some of the finest and most classic songs from singer-songwriters like James Taylor, Carole King, Tom Waits, Jackson Browne, Joni Mitchell and many other timeless favorites. (Cover: Yoko Ono and John Lennon, Central Park, NYC. April 2,1973 / Photo: UMG, press)

items.title: R&B Classics
items.description: Celebrating 25 years of D'Angelo's legendary sophomore album "Voodoo". The perfect collection of classic R&B songs you’ve been searching for. (Cover: D'Angelo // Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Jazz Classics
items.description: Signature tracks from iconic jazz artists, touching on funk, swing, big band and more. (Cover: John Coltrane's 'A Love Supreme' was released 60 years ago, in January 1965 / Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Gothic Americana
items.description: Embrace the shadows with songs that includes dark rock, gloomy folk tales and other night creatures. (Cover: Amenra / Photo: Stefaan Temmerman, press)

items.title: Retroactive
items.description: Your home for prime cuts from fresh reissues, live recordings and previously unreleased material from classic artists. Straight from the vault. (Cover: Frank Black / Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Country Classics
items.description: Country music is one of the most vital and popular American music traditions, evolving from southern-rooted folk songs to the multi-faceted conglomerate of today. Check out the biggest hits and most iconic country songs of all time. (Cover: Kris Kristofferson / Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Modern Day Outlaws
items.description: Expect a wide range of rowdy country rockers, folk hollers, cosmic cowboys and much more - this playlist is dedicated to all sorts of modern day outlaws. (Cover: The Devil Makes Three / Photo: New West, press)

items.title: Modern Psychedelic
items.description: Psychedelic music came out of 1960s counter-culture, but today a new generation of artists are expanding this heady style in new directions. (Cover: Motorpsycho / Photo: Espen Haslene)

items.title: Viral Classics
items.description: Hit songs, some of which spent months dominating the charts, have a way of enjoying a second life years after their release - appearing on a movie soundtrack, selling cars in a TV commercial, or providing TikTokkers with the perfect music accompaniment for their cat videos. You hear them again and are immediately transported back to the first time you heard them. And the time after that. And... (Cover: Arctic Monkeys / Photo: Rovi)

items.title: Punk Riot
items.description: Check out recent punk favorites - from underground garage punks to modern screamo and hardcore rippers. (Cover: Lambrinin Girls / Photo: Derek Perlman, press)

items.title: TIDAL RISING
items.description: Featuring artists in our TIDAL RISING program. More information on TIDAL.com/ForMusic (Cover: Amanda Reifer / Photo: Press)

items.title: R&B: RISING
items.description: The genre of R&B has changed with the times. The TIDAL Rising artists in this playlist are changing the sound of the genre and resonating with a growing audience. (Cover: Lex Aura / Photo: Press)

items.title: Indie: RISING
items.description: The ambiguous nature of indie music is captured here with some of the most exciting, genre-fluid artists in today's world. (Cover: Stevan / Photo: Press)

items.title: Hip-Hop: RISING
items.description: Each week, TIDAL will showcase RISING hip-hop talent worth your undivided attention. This playlist wrangles each upstart's best offerings. (Cover: sosocamo / Photo: Press)

items.title: Pop: RISING
items.description: Pop music's unshakeable appeal is being crafted everyday. TIDAL has waded through the sea of music out there to bring the RISING artists who will be the soundtrack to your life for years to come. (Cover: SkyDxddy / Photo: Press)

items.title: Latin: RISING
items.description: This playlist focuses on blossoming Latinx acts (in Spanish and English) who got next. (Cover: Joaquina  / Photo: UMLE/Press)

items.title: Rock: RISING
items.description: This playlist reflects not only artists we have chosen to be TIDAL Rising, but all the amazing rock musicians we have our eye on at the present. (Cover: Kate Grahn / Photo: Press)

items.title: Folk: RISING
items.description: Folk music has evolved from its origins as a storytelling device to a portrait of modern human stories and the emerging artists in this playlist have excelled at that. (Cover: Daneshevskaya / Photo: Press)

items.title: Mexican Music: RISING
items.description: Young, talented, passionate and proud of their Mexican culture, here's the new generation of artists taking the genre to the next level. (Cover: Octavio Fabio Capri/ Photo: Press)

items.title: Jazz: RISING
items.description: Presenting the most brilliant emerging and developing artists in jazz — in all of the music’s ever-expanding definitions and permutations. (Cover: Sultan Stevenson / Photo: Dave Stapleton)

items.title: Electronic: RISING
items.description: TIDAL's RISING Electronic playlist showcases all aspects of electronic music––from the bedroom producer to touring artists on the precipice of breaking through. These are the ones to keep an eye on. (Cover: Bianca Oblivion / Photo: Press)

items.title: Country: RISING
items.description: Catch up on what's up in the rural corridors of the music map. (Cover: Willow Avalon / Photo: Press)

items.title: Metal: RISING
items.description: These are some of the metal and hard rock acts we here at TIDAL are really looking forward to hearing more from. (Cover: The Narrator / Photo: Believe Digital, press)

items.title: Dolby Atmos: RISING
items.description: Experience some of our featured tracks from RISING in Dolby Atmos (Cover: Lala / Photo: Press)

items.title: Viral Hits

items.title: Global Sunrise
items.description: Start your day off just right with this wonderful selection of songs from all over the world and let the sun embrace your life. (Photo: Unsplash)
